SICP First Edition Examples
===========================

Program examples from:

  Harold Abelson and Gerald Jay Sussman with Julie Sussman.
  Structure and Interpretation of Computer Programs.
  Cambridge, Mass.: MIT Press, 1985.  ISBN 0-262-01077-1.

Source: CMU AI Repository (1995)
  https://www.cs.cmu.edu/afs/cs/project/ai-repository/ai/lang/scheme/bookcode/sicp/

The first edition predates R4RS and uses MIT Scheme conventions.
Load sicp-compat.scm first to get the compatibility definitions
(nil, t, sequence, princ, print, 1+, -1+, atom?, cons-stream,
head, tail, the-empty-stream, etc.).

  (load "sicp-compat.scm")
  (load "chapter1.scm")

Each chapter file contains all examples from that chapter, marked
with ;;; Section N.N.N comments.  Definitions are cumulative and
often redefined (e.g., factorial appears in several variants).

Chapter 1: Building Abstractions with Procedures
Chapter 2: Building Abstractions with Data
Chapter 3: Modularity, Objects, and State
Chapter 4: Metalinguistic Abstraction (metacircular evaluator, logic programming)
Chapter 5: Computing with Register Machines (simulator, compiler)

Note: Chapters 4 and 5 are self-contained systems (a Scheme interpreter
and a register-machine simulator) that define their own eval/apply.
They are not meant to be loaded into a running session alongside
chapters 1-3.
